title: Why the Seattle Case Looms Above Other Immigration Challenges - WSJ
text:
In the 10 days since President Donald Trump handed down his executive order on immigration, plaintiffs have flooded the courts with legal challenges. As of Sunday, more than two dozen petitions and lawsuits had been filed.
